events.name: Tennessee-Martin Skyhawks at Mississippi State Bulldogs

headlines.description: Dak Prescott threw for two touchdowns and ran for another score, leading No. 1 Mississippi State to a 45-16 victory over Tennessee-Martin on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Prescott powers No. 1 Miss. St. by UT Martin

events.name: Virginia Cavaliers at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: Jameis Winston rallied No. 2 Florida State to a 34-20 victory over Virginina on Saturday night for the Seminoles 25th straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: FSU rallies to beat Virginia, win 25th straight

events.name: Texas A&M Aggies at Auburn Tigers

headlines.description: Freshman Kyle Allen threw four touchdown passes in the first half and Texas A&M recovered two fumbles in the final minutes to cap a 41-38 upset of No. 3 Auburn, likely ending the Tigers' playoff hopes.
headlines.shortLinkText: A&M prevails on Auburn fumbles

events.name: Oregon Ducks at Utah Utes

headlines.description: Joe Walker returned Kaelin Clay's careless goal-line fumble 100 yards for a touchdown, Marcus Mariota threw three touchdown passes and ran for another score and No. 4 Oregon turned back No. 17 Utah 51-27 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ducks coast after wild fumble

events.name: Alabama Crimson Tide at LSU Tigers

headlines.description: Blake Sims drove Alabama 55 yards in the final 50 seconds of regulation for a tying field goal, and threw a 6-yard touchdown pass to DeAndrew White in OT to lift Alabama (No. 5 CFP, No. 4 AP) to a 20-13 victory over LSU (No. 16, CFP, No. 14 AP).
headlines.shortLinkText: Bama rallies, escapes LSU upset bid

events.name: Kansas State Wildcats at TCU Horned Frogs

headlines.description: Trevone Boykin ran for 123 yards and three touchdowns and threw for another score, leading No. 6 TCU to a 41-20 victory over No. 7 Kansas State on Saturday night that had huge Big 12 title and playoff implications.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boykin, TCU take charge of Big 12

events.name: Ohio State Buckeyes at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: J.T. Barrett threw for three touchdowns and ran for two in a sensational performance, and 14th-ranked Ohio State scored almost at will against Michigan State's vaunted defense, beating the eighth-ranked Spartans 49-37 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: OSU scores statement win over MSU

events.name: Notre Dame Fighting Irish at Arizona State Sun Devils

headlines.description: Taylor Kelly threw a 4-yard touchdown pass to Demario Richard in the fourth quarter and Lloyd Carrington followed with a 58-yard interception return for another score, helping No. 9 Arizona State withstand a furious second-half rally to beat Notre Dame.
headlines.shortLinkText: ASU holds off rally, tops Notre Dame

events.name: Presbyterian College Blue Hose at Ole Miss Rebels

headlines.description: Bo Wallace threw for two touchdowns and ran for another as Mississippi (No. 11 CFP, No. 12 AP) snapped a two-game losing streak Saturday with a 48-0 win over Presbyterian.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ole Miss snaps losing skid with shutout win

events.name: Baylor Bears at Oklahoma Sooners

headlines.description: Corey Coleman set career highs of 15 catches and 224 yards to help Baylor (No. 12 CFP, No. 10 AP) get a landmark win by rolling past Oklahoma (No. 15 CFP, No. 16 AP) 48-14 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Baylor cruises past Oklahoma

events.name: UCLA Bruins at Washington Huskies

headlines.description: Brett Hundley threw for two touchdowns to become UCLA's all-time leader in TD passes, ran for two more scores and Myles Jack added a highlight-reel 28-yard touchdown run in No. 18 UCLA's 44-30 win over Washington on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hundley sets UCLA TD passing mark in win

headlines.shortLinkText: Solomon powers No. 19 Arizona past Colorado 38-20

events.name: Georgia Bulldogs at Kentucky Wildcats

headlines.description: Hutson Mason threw a career-best four touchdown passes, Nick Chubb rushed for 170 yards and a TD and Georgia (No. 20 CFP, No. 17 AP) steamrolled Kentucky 63-31 on Saturday.

video.headline: Georgia Returns Opening Kickoff 90 Yards For TD

tracking.trackingName: Georgia Returns Opening Kickoff 90-Yards For TD

headlines.shortLinkText: UGA rebounds with rout behind Mason TDs

events.name: Duke Blue Devils at Syracuse Orange

headlines.description: Anthony Boone threw two touchdowns to Issac Blakeney, Jamison Crowder returned a punt 52 yards for another score, and No. 22 Duke survived another scare, beating Syracuse 27-10 on Saturday with a late rally.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 22 Duke beats Syracuse 27-10

events.name: West Virginia Mountaineers at Texas Longhorns

headlines.description: Johnathan Gray scored three touchdowns and Texas inched closer to a possible bowl game in head coach Charlie Strong's first season with a 33-16 win over No. 23 West Virginia on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gray helps Texas upend No. 23 WVU

headlines.description: D.J. White and Quayshawn Nealy scored defensive touchdowns in the second quarter to help Georgia Tech (No. 24 CFP) beat North Carolina State 56-23 on Saturday.
